-- Singapore Refining to Decide on Upgrade Investment in Early 2013
-- B y   R a m s e y   A l - R i k a b i
-- 2012-08-16T02:55:26Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-16/singapore-refining-to-decide-on-upgrade-investment-in-early-2013.html
Singapore Refining Co. plans to
decide early next year on investments to upgrade its 290,000
barrel-a-day facility.  The joint venture of  Chevron Corp. (CVX)  and Singapore Petroleum
Co., a subsidiary of PetroChina Co., “is on schedule to make a
final investment decision on the construction of a gasoline-
production upgrade project and associated electricity and steam
cogeneration plant by early 2013,” it said today in an e-mailed
statement.  Singapore Refining will spend $500 million on the expansion,
the Business Times newspaper reported today, citing a source it
did not identify.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ramsey Al-Rikabi in Singapore at 
